    {
      "id": "PopularPost368077",
      "post_content": "I feel like nobody really reads the comprehensive rules. We need more Melvins.  \n  \nThis \\*is\\* strictly better than [Blue Elemental Blast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blue Elemental Blast) because the color is not a targeting restriction. However, you cannot Glammerdye this after it targets a Kozilek because \"colorless\" is neither a color nor a color word. You want to target Kozilek? Change \\*his\\* color.  \n  \nAs far as this card, it's pretty great. It hoses red as sideboard fodder and if you build a color change deck, it is a solid piece of maindeck removal for a single drop of water. And yeah, illusions.  \n  \nComparing the Red and Blue variants of this:  \nBlue Elemental Blast  \n[Flash Flood](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flash Flood)  \nHydroblast  \nVs.  \n[Red Elemental Blast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Red Elemental Blast)  \n[Active Volcano](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Active Volcano)  \n[Pyroblast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pyroblast)  \n  \nRed gets a point for utility, a point for a counter (or bounce), a point for color specific enchantment destruction and a point for color specific creature destruction (make it half a point since red can ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "MacBizzle",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost368077\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">I feel like nobody really reads the comprehensive rules. We need more Melvins.<br/><br/>This *is* strictly better than <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Blue Elemental Blast\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Blue Elemental Blast\">Blue Elemental Blast</a> because the color is not a targeting restriction. However, you cannot Glammerdye this after it targets a Kozilek because \"colorless\" is neither a color nor a color word. You want to target Kozilek? Change *his* color.<br/><br/>As far as this card, it's pretty great. It hoses red as sideboard fodder and if you build a color change deck, it is a solid piece of maindeck removal for a single drop of water. And yeah, illusions.<br/><br/>Comparing the Red and Blue variants of this:<br/>Blue Elemental Blast<br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Flash Flood\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Flash Flood\">Flash Flood</a><br/>Hydroblast<br/>Vs.<br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Red Elemental Blast\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Red Elemental Blast\">Red Elemental Blast</a><br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Active Volcano\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Active Volcano\">Active Volcano</a><br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Pyroblast\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pyroblast\">Pyroblast</a><br/><br/>Red gets a point for utility, a point for a counter (or bounce), a point for color specific enchantment destruction and a point for color specific creature destruction (make it half a point since red can ... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 368077)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '368077'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy46803\">MacBizzle</span>\r\n                                (3/19/2014 2:23:40 AM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>"
